[94,681,682],{"class":545},"height",[94,684,632],{"class":100},[94,686,231],{"class":550},[94,688,314],{"class":545},[94,690,112],{"class":550},[94,692,693,695,697],{"class":96,"line":228},[94,694,231],{"class":550},[94,696,305],{"class":545},[94,698,112],{"class":550},[94,700,701,703,706,708],{"class":96,"line":238},[94,702,542],{"class":100},[94,704,705],{"class":550},"\u002F",[94,707,584],{"class":545},[94,709,559],{"class":100},[17,711,712,713,715],{},"Finally, let's try visiting ",[31,714,33],{}," again and see what happens:",[17,717,718],{},[38,719],{"alt":720,"src":721},"header still comes through","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FXfCpx8E.png",[17,723,724,725,727,728,731,732,734,735,737,738,741,742,744],{},"So how does it work? Because we declared at the top of ",[31,726,33],{}," that we want to load the layout template (",[31,729,730],{},"{layout name=\"layout\" \u002F}","), ThinkPHP loads ",[31,733,494],{}," into ",[31,736,33],{}," and replaces ",[31,739,740],{},"{__CONTENT__}"," with the original ",[31,743,33],{}," content.",[17,746,747,748,750,751,753,754,756,757,760,761,530],{},"Of course, if you don't want to use ",[31,749,740],{}," and would rather use something fancier, ThinkPHP gives you another option — you just have to tell it where the content should go. For example, say my ",[31,752,494],{}," doesn't want to use ",[31,755,740],{}," but ",[31,758,759],{},"{__ONEFORALL__}"," instead (I've been watching too much My Hero Academia lately). Then you'd change ",[31,762,494],{},[85,764,766],{"className":87,"code":765,"language":89,"meta":90,"style":90},"{include file=\"index\u002Flayout\u002Fheader\" \u002F}\n[__ONEFORALL__] \u002F\u002F note: wrap it in []\n{include file=\"index\u002Flayout\u002Ffooter\" \u002F}\n",[31,767,768,772,777],{"__ignoreMap":90},[94,769,770],{"class":96,"line":97},[94,771,381],{"class":100},[94,773,774],{"class":96,"line":115},[94,775,776],{"class":100},"[__ONEFORALL__] \u002F\u002F note: wrap it in []\n",[94,778,779],{"class":96,"line":135},[94,780,463],{"class":100},[17,782,783,784,786,787,790],{},"And the layout import inside ",[31,785,33],{},"? You use ",[31,788,789],{},"replace"," to tell ThinkPHP which chunk we're going to parse and swap out, so you'd write it like this:",[85,792,794],{"className":87,"code":793,"language":89,"meta":90,"style":90},"{layout name=\"layout\" replace=\"[__ONEFORALL__]\" \u002F}\n\u003Ch1>{$title}\u003C\u002Fh1>\n{volist name=\"user\" id=\"list\"}\n\u003Cul>\n  \u003Cli>Name:{$list.name}\u003C\u002Fli>\n  \u003Cli>Weight:{$list.weight}\u003C\u002Fli>\n  \u003Cli>Height:{$list.height}\u003C\u002Fli>\n\u003C\u002Ful>\n{\u002Fvolist}\n",[31,795,796,801,813,817,825,837,849,861,869],{"__ignoreMap":90},[94,797,798],{"class":96,"line":97},[94,799,800],{"class":100},"{layout name=\"layout\" replace=\"[__ONEFORALL__]\" \u002F}\n",[94,802,803,805,807,809,811],{"class":96,"line":115},[94,804,118],{"class":100},[94,806,287],{"class":104},[94,808,221],{"class":100},[94,810,287],{"class":104},[94,812,112],{"class":100},[94,814,815],{"class":96,"line":135},[94,816,298],{"class":100},[94,818,819,821,823],{"class":96,"line":145},[94,820,118],{"class":100},[94,822,305],{"class":104},[94,824,112],{"class":100},[94,826,827,829,831,833,835],{"class":96,"line":164},[94,828,148],{"class":100},[94,830,314],{"class":104},[94,832,317],{"class":100},[94,834,314],{"class":104},[94,836,112],{"class":100},[94,838,839,841,843,845,847],{"class":96,"line":189},[94,840,148],{"class":100},[94,842,314],{"class":104},[94,844,330],{"class":100},[94,846,314],{"class":104},[94,848,112],{"class":100},[94,850,851,853,855,857,859],{"class":96,"line":213},[94,852,148],{"class":100},[94,854,314],{"class":104},[94,856,343],{"class":100},[94,858,314],{"class":104},[94,860,112],{"class":100},[94,862,863,865,867],{"class":96,"line":228},[94,864,231],{"class":100},[94,866,305],{"class":104},[94,868,112],{"class":100},[94,870,871],{"class":96,"line":238},[94,872,360],{"class":100},[17,874,875],{},"And the result is the same — the layout gets pulled in just fine:",[17,877,878],{},[38,879],{"alt":880,"src":881},"pulled in successfully","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FDlAGx5T.png",[17,883,884,885,888,889,896],{},"You can also tweak things through ",[31,886,887],{},"config\u002Ftemplate.php",", and you can even use a Controller to decide which layout gets output. For the full details, check the official ",[890,891,895],"a",{"href":892,"rel":893},"https:\u002F\u002Fwww.kancloud.cn\u002Fmanual\u002Fthinkphp5_1\u002F354079",[894],"nofollow","developer manual"," (in Mandarin) — I'm only covering the common approaches here.",[12,898,900],{"id":899},"wrapping-up","Wrapping up",[17,902,903],{},"From this post you can see that ThinkPHP's built-in template engine is actually plenty good enough. Unless you've got some special requirement, I'd generally just recommend sticking with the built-in one. Next up I'll cover ThinkPHP + Bootstrap, which ties in nicely with the Layout technique from this post — that way the effect will be a lot easier to see.",[905,906,907],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .s8XSl, html code.shiki .s8XSl{--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-default:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .syv7_, html code.shiki .syv7_{--shiki-light:#22863A;--shiki-default:#22863A;--shiki-dark:#72F088}html pre.shiki code .sK3KL, html code.shiki .sK3KL{--shiki-light:#6F42C1;--shiki-default:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#91CBFF}html pre.shiki code .sWayO, html code.shiki .sWayO{--shiki-light:#032F62;--shiki-default:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#ADDCFF}html .light .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-light);background: var(--shiki-light-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-light-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-light-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-light-text-decoration);}html.light .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-light);background: var(--shiki-light-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-light-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-light-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-light-text-decorati